# Architecture Rules

**Scope of this file:** only constraints that protect **code that already exists** (or is being edited in-tree) from Cursor drift. One rule is stated once — do not re-expand it in Common Mistakes.

**Forward design** (GameManager injection order, entity tick chain, AbilitySystem / BuffSystem / HUD wiring, TryExecute flow, on-cast buff site, etc.) lives in local gitignored `ARCHITECTURE_Detailed.md`. Follow Detailed when implementing a new module; after the module lands and is verified, promote only the pitfalls Cursor actually hits into this file.

## Layer Boundaries

See `.asmdef` files for the authoritative dependency graph.

- `Core` — no dependencies on other game layers (event bus + state machine only; **no** gameplay event structs).
- `Gameplay` — depends only on `Core` (stats, damageable, combat, buffs, gameplay events).
- `Ability` — depends on `Core` and `Gameplay`.
- `Demo` — depends on Core, Gameplay, and Ability.

Direction: **Core ← Gameplay ← Ability ← Demo**. Do not introduce reverse references. If unsure which layer a type belongs to, check the asmdef files.

DoT (Burn) bypasses `DamagePipeline` by **semantic** choice (DoT typically skips armor/crit attribution), not by asmdef isolation — buff and combat types share `Game.Gameplay`. Do not route DoT through Pipeline unless explicitly requested.

## Portfolio Scope — Do Not Implement

This is a **portfolio-scale single-player demo** (~3k–5k LOC, fixed ability slots, 1v1). Do not add production GAS-scale systems unless the user explicitly requests them. Document trade-offs in README instead of half-implementing.

**Do not generate:**

| System | Reason |
|---|---|
| `GameplayTag` / tag containers / BlockedByTags / CancelsTags | Demo uses `CanExecute` + cooldown only |
| `TargetFilter` / `TargetPolicy` / AOE / cone / ground targeting | Single-target 1v1; `TryExecute` takes one `AbilityTargetDeps` |
| `GameplayEffectSpec` / attribute snapshotting at cast time | Modifiers read live `Stats` at hit time |
| Resource / cost gating (mana, energy, charges) | Cooldown only |
| `ICooldownManager` or DI frameworks (VContainer, Zenject) | Concrete `CooldownManager` + constructor injection |
| BuffSystem split into Manager + Container | Merged `BuffSystem` is intentional |
| Network prediction / replication / save-load | Explicit non-goals |
| Cast time / channel / GCD / `PlayerCastState` | All demo abilities are instant |
| Activation Commit phase (TryActivate→Commit cost→Execute) | Execute success → cooldown only |
| Modifier priority phases (Base → Equipment → Buff → Final) | **Multiplicative modifiers only** |
| AbilityId registry replacing fixed `AbilityIndex` | Three fixed slots |
| SO Event Channels as global event backbone | Injected `IEventBus` instances |
| Merging `AbilityExecuteResult` and `TryExecuteResult` | Two enums by design — `OnCooldown` only on `TryExecuteResult` |

If asked to "make it more like GAS," extend README **GAS Comparison / What I'd Do Differently** — do not silently expand runtime scope.

## Event Placement

Events are `readonly struct` types **implementing `IEvent`**. `Core/Events/` holds **only** the bus contract (`IEvent`, `IEventBus`, `EventBus`).

| Location | Events |
|---|---|
| `Core/Events/` | `IEvent`, `IEventBus`, `EventBus` only |
| `Gameplay/Events/` | `HpChangedEvent`, `HealEvent`, `DamageEvent`, `EntityDiedEvent`, `BuffAppliedEvent`, `BuffRemovedEvent` |
| `Gameplay/Stats/Events/` | `StatChangedEvent` |
| `Ability/Events/` | `CooldownStartedEvent`, `CooldownEndedEvent` |

Do not define gameplay events in `Core/`. Keep death event name **`EntityDiedEvent`** (not `EnemyDiedEvent`); payload is `ICombatEntity`.

## Pure C# vs MonoBehaviour

Game logic lives in pure C# classes with no Unity lifecycle dependency.

MonoBehaviour is allowed only for Unity-facing adapters: view, input handling, lifecycle entry points, VFX/animation drivers, and the composition root. Examples: `Player`, `Enemy`, `GameManager`, HUD/UI binding. New adapters (e.g. `ProjectileView`) are fine under the same rule — no gameplay logic; forward to pure C#.

A MonoBehaviour may orchestrate lifecycle and forward calls; damage math, buff logic, AI decisions, state transition *conditions*, and stat math belong in pure C#.

## Dependency Injection

Inject via constructor. Do not resolve dependencies with `FindObjectOfType<T>()`, `GameObject.Find()`, or any service locator / static accessor.

`GetComponent<T>()` is allowed only inside MonoBehaviour adapters during `Awake`/`Start`, cached in a field — never inside `Update` or inside a pure C# class.

Do not implement shared services as static classes or singletons. `EventBus`, `DamagePipeline`, and `IRandomProvider` are instances with explicit lifetimes. Do not use `UnityEngine.Random` in pure C# gameplay code — use `IRandomProvider`.

## Event Bus

Use `IEventBus` everywhere except composition roots (`GameManager`, `Player`, `Enemy`) where concrete `EventBus` is instantiated. HUD and other consumers hold `IEventBus`, not `EventBus`.

`EventBus.Publish` is synchronous and **zero-allocation** — combined delegate in `Dictionary<Type, Delegate>`; **never** call `Delegate.GetInvocationList()` inside `Publish`. Do not switch to deferred/queued dispatch without an explicit request.

**EventBus is a notification system, not a control system.** A class changes its own gameplay state because its own method decided to. Handlers must not mutate another class's state on behalf of the publisher — events mean "this happened," not "go do this."

Local vs global bus ownership, HUD binding timing, and which events ride which bus are specified in `ARCHITECTURE_Detailed.md` (not yet fully coded).

## Verified Invariants (existing code)

### StateMachine

- `StateMachine<TOwner>` / `IState<TOwner>` use **unconstrained** generics — do not add `where TOwner : class` or `where TOwner : MonoBehaviour`.
- Per-frame API is **`Tick`**, not `Update`: `IState.Tick(TOwner, float deltaTime)` / `StateMachine.Tick(float deltaTime)`.
- Constructor `(owner, initialState)` invokes `initialState.Enter(owner)` immediately; null `initialState` → `ArgumentNullException`.
- `ChangeState(newState)` no-ops when `newState` is the same instance as `CurrentState` (no Exit/Enter).
- Reentrant `ChangeState` from within `Enter`/`Exit` is not supported — transition from `Tick` or external gameplay logic.

### Stats / Damageable / Combat

- `ICombatEntity` exposes only `Stats` (`IReadOnlyStatCollection`) and `Damageable` — not `StateMachine`, `EventBus`, or `IBuffApplier`.
- `Damageable.MaxHealth` (or `MaxHP`) is a read-only property that reads `StatCollection.GetValue(StatType.MaxHealth)` on every access — **never** cache MaxHP as a field on `Damageable`.
- Prefer mutating MaxHealth via `StatCollection` APIs (`SetBaseStat` / modifier APIs). When the clamped resolved value changes, `StatCollection` publishes `StatChangedEvent`; `Damageable` should clamp CurrentHP on `StatType.MaxHealth` — do not bypass Stats for MaxHealth.
- `Damageable.TakeDamage` updates HP and publishes **`HpChangedEvent`** on the entity's local bus. It does **not** publish `DamageEvent`. `DamagePipeline.Execute` (when present) publishes `DamageEvent` after applying damage. DoT paths publish only `HpChangedEvent`.
- `DefenseModifier`: `damage × 100 / (100 + Defense)`; skips `DamageType.True`.
- `CritModifier`: multiplies by `Source.Stats.GetValue(StatType.CritDamage)` when `ctx.IsCrit` (**True damage still receives crit**). Pipeline allows **multiplicative modifiers only** — no flat/subtractive modifiers without a phased pipeline.

### Pure C# construction

- Pure C# classes take dependencies through the **constructor**. Do not add `Initialize(Dependency)` methods except where Unity constructs the object (`MonoBehaviour` / `ScriptableObject`) and a constructor is unavailable.
- All gameplay event structs must implement `IEvent`.

## Common Generation Mistakes

Short index only — full rule is above (or in `ARCHITECTURE_Detailed.md` for not-yet-coded modules).

| Mistake | See |
|---|---|
| `where TOwner : class` / `MonoBehaviour` on StateMachine | StateMachine |
| `Update` on `IState` / `StateMachine` | StateMachine (`Tick`) |
| `Initialize()` on pure C# instead of ctor injection | Pure C# construction |
| Caching `MaxHP` on `Damageable` | Stats / Damageable |
| Publishing `DamageEvent` from `Damageable` | Stats / Damageable |
| Gameplay event structs in `Core/Events/` | Event Placement |
| Event struct without `IEvent` | Pure C# construction |
| `FindObjectOfType` / service locator / static shared services | Dependency Injection |
| `UnityEngine.Random` in pure C# gameplay | Dependency Injection |
| HUD / Ability / Buff / GameManager composition mistakes | `ARCHITECTURE_Detailed.md` |
